            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1386316124,
            "creation_date": 1386316124,
            "body": "<p>HashMaps work on the principle of keys and values. For every key, there is a value.  <\/p>\n\n<p>If you want to get ths value associated with the key, use the <code>get(key)<\/code> method. This will return the value for the key or null if key does not exist.  <\/p>\n\n<p>You declaration and initialization of the map is wrong, though. It should be as follows:<br>\n<code>Map&lt;Object,List&lt;Object&gt;&gt; map = ...<\/code><br>\nSince Map is an interface, you will need to use a HashMap or something in place of ... on the right side.  <\/p>\n\n<p>Please have a look : <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/collections/interfaces/map.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/collections/interfaces/map.html<\/a><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 20418741,
            "question_id": 20418375
        }
